version_description: This version is different to the original because it's lvie and it is also harder to play. In my opinion it sounds much better so I want to let you know how it gets played.
I beleive this is the correct way to play this with open chords in the first position if you do not want to play the original power chord version.
For easier version, put capo on the first fret and transpose -1. You can replace all the chords with corresponding power chords.
This is an acoustic version of the song, played in this video: Live Acoustic Version: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m7hmlSWzY4E.
Chords are optimized for acoustic players. Can be played with any strumming pattern you feel fits.
It gives the best explanation to all the guitar parts of this new song.
The Am/B Am Am/G lines in the choruses are really just keeping the Am chord and moving the bottom note up and down. Also, fairly optional if you want to exclude it and just use Am.
All tabs are in standard tuning anf transposed as to not require a capo.
No capo is required throughout this whole album tab.
